01:01:11.295 --> 01:01:12.949
by doing backward induction.
 

01:01:12.949 --> 01:01:15.557
You couldn't tell what the
value of this bond is here with

01:01:15.557 --> 01:01:18.076
all these defaults and stuff
until you started computing

01:01:18.076 --> 01:01:21.130
backwards until you got to here,
so the same way here.

01:01:21.130 --> 01:01:24.989
We know at the edges it's very
obvious when all the cards are

01:01:24.989 --> 01:01:27.947
black or all the cards are red,
that's up here,

01:01:27.947 --> 01:01:30.199
it's obvious what the value is.
 

01:01:30.199 --> 01:01:33.565
But if you have a position here
you can figure out what the

01:01:33.565 --> 01:01:36.349
value is of being in that
position of 1 and 1.

01:01:36.349 --> 01:01:38.210
You could quit and be 0,
or you could say,

01:01:38.210 --> 01:01:40.750
what are my chances of getting
a black card and winning 1

01:01:40.750 --> 01:01:41.250
dollar?
 

01:01:41.250 --> 01:01:43.610
If I get a black card then I
move to this position,

01:01:43.610 --> 01:01:46.349
but I already figured out this
position's value because I'm

01:01:46.349 --> 01:01:48.050
doing backward induction,
right?

01:01:48.050 --> 01:01:51.820
That's got one less--sorry,
if I draw a black card I go

01:01:51.820 --> 01:01:52.590
this way.
 

01:01:52.590 --> 01:01:55.465
It's got 1 less black card and
we already know that value of

01:01:55.465 --> 01:01:56.489
that position is 0.
 

01:01:56.489 --> 01:01:59.262
So to figure out the value of
this position I know the chance

01:01:59.262 --> 01:02:01.621
of getting a black card,
then I'm going to end up in

01:02:01.621 --> 01:02:03.239
that position which is value 0.
 

01:02:03.239 --> 01:02:05.610
I won't draw any more.
 

01:02:05.610 --> 01:02:09.054
Or I'm going to get a red card
and then I'm going to move to

01:02:09.054 --> 01:02:12.559
this position over here whose
value I've already computed.

01:02:12.559 --> 01:02:14.460
So that gives me the value here.
 

01:02:14.460 --> 01:02:16.449
How do I figure out the value
here?

01:02:16.449 --> 01:02:19.630
Well, it's now 2 reds and 1
black.

01:02:19.630 --> 01:02:21.000
So this looks really bad.
 

01:02:21.000 --> 01:02:24.907
Actually this position,
the value of this I happen to

01:02:24.907 --> 01:02:25.809
know is 0.
 

01:02:25.809 --> 01:02:27.985
How could it be,
with 2 red cards and only 1

01:02:27.985 --> 01:02:30.670
black card actually the value of
the position is 0?

01:02:30.670 --> 01:02:31.909
Well, what do I do?
 

01:02:31.909 --> 01:02:36.018
The chances of getting a black
card the first time are 1 third.

01:02:36.018 --> 01:02:40.349
So V of (1,2) is going to be 1
third of getting a black card

01:02:40.349 --> 01:02:44.972
plus then I go to here which is
no black cards left and just red

01:02:44.972 --> 01:02:48.650
cards,
which obviously is 0,

01:02:48.650 --> 01:02:50.699
plus 2 thirds.
 

01:02:50.699 --> 01:02:53.800
2 thirds of the time I get a
red card and lose 1 dollar,

01:02:53.800 --> 01:02:56.842
but then I'm going to move to
here with 1 red card where I

01:02:56.842 --> 01:02:59.182
have V of (1 and 1),
which I've already figured out

01:02:59.182 --> 01:03:00.000
the answer to,
right?

01:03:00.000 --> 01:03:04.989
This was V of (1 and 1) has
value a half.

01:03:04.989 --> 01:03:09.617
So therefore V of (1 and 2) is
going to be 2 thirds times minus

01:03:09.617 --> 01:03:11.260
1 V of (1,2),
right?

01:03:11.260 --> 01:03:15.021
I just drew a black card so
it's no longer--no,

01:03:15.021 --> 01:03:18.210
I drew a red card,
so it's (1 and 1).

01:03:18.210 --> 01:03:20.260
So I started with 1 black and 2
reds,

01:03:20.260 --> 01:03:22.099
1 third of the time I get a
black card,

01:03:22.099 --> 01:03:24.510
2 thirds of the times I get a
red card,

01:03:24.510 --> 01:03:28.143
but after getting the red card
the position is now 1 black and

01:03:28.143 --> 01:03:28.619
1 red.
 

01:03:28.619 --> 01:03:30.110
The red card disappeared.
 

01:03:30.110 --> 01:03:31.190
That's over here.
 

01:03:31.190 --> 01:03:33.489
So I get a black card,
I move to here.

01:03:33.489 --> 01:03:35.909
If I get a red card I move to
there,

01:03:35.909 --> 01:03:42.842
but V of (1,1) is worth a half,
so that's equal to 1 third

01:03:42.842 --> 01:03:48.559
times (1 0) 2 thirds times
(minus 1 1 half),

01:03:48.559 --> 01:03:54.719
which equals 1 third - 1 third
which equals 0.

01:03:54.719 --> 01:03:58.492
So starting at this point
you've got 1 red card and 2

01:03:58.492 --> 01:03:59.510
black cards.
 

01:03:59.510 --> 01:04:02.159
It looks horrible to pick a
card, 2 thirds of the time

01:04:02.159 --> 01:04:04.059
you're going to get the wrong
card,

01:04:04.059 --> 01:04:07.780
but you still have a position
that's actually equal in value,

01:04:07.780 --> 01:04:12.880
because if you get that black
card which wins you stop.

01:04:12.880 --> 01:04:15.731
If you get a red card you're
now in a position that's equal

01:04:15.731 --> 01:04:17.550
deck and that's favorable for
you,

01:04:17.550 --> 01:04:20.000
because if you get another
black card you stop,

01:04:20.000 --> 01:04:26.889
and if you get a red card you
keep playing until the end.

01:04:26.889 --> 01:04:27.670
So that's it.
 

01:04:27.670 --> 01:04:29.780
So how can you do this by
backward induction?

01:04:29.780 --> 01:04:33.626
You have the stuff on the edges
and then you solve for all these

01:04:33.626 --> 01:04:36.858
things along the side here,
and having done that now I can

01:04:36.858 --> 01:04:39.469
solve for this one because I've
got up and to the left.

01:04:39.469 --> 01:04:42.539
Now I do that row and then I
can do this whole row,

01:04:42.539 --> 01:04:45.840
and then I can just by backward
induction do the whole thing,

01:04:45.840 --> 01:04:47.719
and the computer does that
instantly.

01:04:47.719 --> 01:04:50.813
So it figures out the value of
every single node and it's

01:04:50.813 --> 01:04:52.469
shocking what the answer is.
 

01:04:52.469 --> 01:05:00.590
So are there any other
questions about this?

